com.storytron.swat.loglizard

Class LogDownloadManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.storytron.swat.loglizard.LogDownloadManager
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.awt.event.ActionListener, java.util.EventListener

    public class LogDownloadManager
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.awt.event.ActionListener
    A class for managing downloading of log data.

    Log data is generated from the server as the story advances and also as the author expands the log tree.

    The surface log data generated while playing a story is reported to this class through the reportNodes(Compressed[]) method.

    When full branches of the log tree are requested the method request(int, TreePath, boolean) is called. This method submits the request only if the branch has not been previously requested. This is to avoid unnecessary traffic and improve reaction times.

    The method processRequest(Triplet) is called when full branches arrive from the engine. These branches are in turn reported to the tree model and then they are expanded.

    This class is accessed both by the logDownloader thread Swat.LogDownloaderThread) and by the event dispatcher thread. The logDownloader is the thread in which downloaded data is reported. The event dispatcher thread is the thread where request for full log tree branches are submitted.

    Interval sets

    The implementation of this class relies on a small set of routines for manipulating sets of disjoint integer intervals. These sets are used to describe the branches that have been already requested and the branches that have been already received.

    An integer interval is represented as a Pair, and a set of intervals is represented as set of pairs (Set>). The functions for manipulating these sets are:

    • findInterval(Set, int)
    • removeInterval(Set, int, int)
    • removeInterval(Set, int, int, int, int)
    • isFull(Set)
    • addInterval(Set, int, int)
